                </div>

                <p>Highway DSL is a formal specification language for defining workflow execution graphs. It provides a Python-based fluent API for programmatic workflow construction and serializes to YAML/JSON for storage, versioning, and interchange.</p>

                <div class="note">
                    <strong>SPECIFICATION NOTICE:</strong> Highway DSL defines the canonical format for workflow representation. Execution engines should implement Highway DSL parsers to achieve workflow portability and interoperability.
